This paper discusses the Semantic Web and its evolution into a computing platform, which involves technologies such as canonical representation and dynamic structures. These topics are closely related to several computer science sub-categories, including Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Software Engineering (cs.SE), Databases (cs.DB), and Cybersecurity (cs.CY). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
